# BidPazar Web Product Context

## Purpose
Frontend application for a real-time auction marketplace with live streaming, allowing users to browse products, watch live auctions, place bids, and communicate with sellers.

## Technical Problems Solved
- Real-time UI updates for auction and bidding status
- WebRTC video streaming consumption
- Authentication state management
- Responsive design for mobile and desktop
- Form validation and submission
- WebSocket event handling
- Chat interface for live streams and private messaging
- Auction countdown UI

## Architecture
- Next.js App Router for page routing
- React components with TypeScript
- Context API for state management
- Custom hooks for shared logic
- API services for backend communication
- Socket.io for real-time updates
- WebRTC for stream consumption
- TailwindCSS for responsive UI

## Data Flow
1. User authentication → JWT storage → Protected routes
2. Product browsing → API data fetching → UI rendering
3. Stream viewing → WebRTC connection → Media consumption
4. Bid placement → Form validation → API submission → Socket update
5. Chat messaging → Socket events → UI updates
6. Notifications → Real-time reception → Alert display

## User Experience Goals
- Fast page loads with optimized assets
- Seamless bidding experience during auctions
- Reliable video streaming with fallback options
- Intuitive navigation and information hierarchy
- Responsive design for all device sizes

- Real-time feedback for user actions